column2: Accounting Standards (AS): Disclosures Checklist Revised October 2022
Peer Review Statutory and Tax Audit
CARO 2020, An Illustrative Checklist On the Companies (Auditor`s Report) Order, 2020
Audit Program - Statement of Profit and Loss
Accounts Receivable Invoices/Packing slips/Cash Receipt details
1. Significant issue(s) involving selection, application, and consistency of accounting principles (including disclosures)
10. Significant findings or issues identified during the reviews of interim financial information: [ ]

11. Disagreements among members of the engagement team or with others consulted about final conclusions reached on significant accounting or auditing matters, including the basis for the final resolution

2. Results of procedures indicating a need for significant modification of planned procedures: material misstatements (including omissions in the financial statements): significant deficiencies or material weaknesses in internal control
3. Accumulated misstatements and evaluation of uncorrected misstatements, including relevant quantitative and qualitative factors
4. Circumstances that caused significant difficulty in applying auditing procedures
6. Risks of material misstatement determined to be significant risks and the results of auditing procedures in response to such risks
7. Other significant findings or issues, including any significant unusual transactions
5. Significant changes in the auditor’s risk assessments, including risks that were not previously identified, and modifications or additions to audit procedures due to such changes
8. Other matters that could result in modification of the audit report
